# Subtask 0: Foundation & Infrastructure Setup

## Objective
Set up the complete project foundation including Vite+React+TypeScript configuration, all dependencies, folder structure, Tailwind CSS with theme support, and the static meals dataset.

## Steps

### 1. Initialize Vite Project with React + TypeScript

```bash
npm create vite@latest . -- --template react-ts
```

Answer prompts:
- Overwrite directory: Yes
- Select framework: React
- Select variant: TypeScript

### 2. Install All Dependencies

```bash
# Core dependencies
npm install react-router-dom zustand @supabase/supabase-js @tanstack/react-query

# Form & Validation
npm install react-hook-form zod @hookform/resolvers

# UI & Animation
npm install framer-motion lucide-react clsx

# Dev dependencies
npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npm install -D @types/node

# Initialize Tailwind
npx tailwindcss init -p
```

### 3. Configure TypeScript (tsconfig.json)

Update `tsconfig.json`:

```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020",
    "useDefineForClassFields": true,
    "lib": ["ES2020", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "moduleResolution": "bundler",
    "allowImportingTsExtensions": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "noEmit": true,
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "strict": true,
    "noUnusedLocals": true,
    "noUnusedParameters": true,
    "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true,
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src"],
  "references": [{ "path": "./tsconfig.node.json" }]
}
```

